{"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"conditions":[],"oppositionLevel":5,"gifts":[],"isMainNPC":true,"notes":"Gifts: Water of Life (heal/resurrect), Fury of Sea (30ft area OL 7), Waves (teleport 6 miles + 2 people)","background":"","descriptors":["Fairy of the sea, my magic performs miracles"],"npcType":"villager","agenda":["Sad that Enar chose hatred over love"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1},"max":3}}},"name":"Sea Fairy","flags":{"scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","inspiration":"The Little Mermaid"},"type":"npc","_id":"0d4686f45ef0e4af"}
{"name":"Erik - The Innocent","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/child-sleeping.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Erik is a lively, curious six-year-old boy who can never sit still. He is the son of Satu and Captain Andersen, conceived through rape six years ago, though Erik knows nothing of his dark origins. For most of his life, Erik lived in poverty with his mother, working alongside her in difficult conditions. Then, months ago, a wealthy man—Andersen—appeared and took them both to live in a beautiful mansion on a grand estate. Erik doesn't fully understand who Andersen is or why he brought them here. He senses there is a complicated relationship between the man and his mother, but no one will explain it to him. Erik is fascinated by the Hunters and will approach them with endless questions, not fully grasping the danger surrounding the estate. He is an innocent caught in the middle of adult sins and vengeance. Erik collects shells and on Day 2, he will recognize the shells that fall from Enar's body as matching those found at the cliff where the Sea Fairy lives—this becomes a crucial clue. If Erik is put in danger, both Satu and Andersen will put their lives at risk to protect him. If Enar discovers that Erik is Andersen's son, the child becomes his new primary target, as killing him is the perfect way to make Andersen feel the pain he inflicted.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a lively child who can never sit still","I am curious about everything and everyone","I collect shells and know the stories about the Sea Fairy","I don't understand why my mother is so sad"],"gifts":[],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Understand who Andersen really is, and why he took my mom and me out of the misery we lived in","Explore the estate and meet the interesting visitors (the Hunters)","Make my mother smile again like she used to"],"notes":"Erik is the emotional center of the scenario—his innocence contrasts with the darkness around him. Voice: High-pitched, excited, full of questions. Randomly encountered on estate (roll 3-4 on d6). Provides crucial Day 2 clue by recognizing Enar's shells as matching those from the cliff caves. If endangered, both parents will confess everything to save him. If Enar learns he's Andersen's son (through overheard conversation or confession), Erik becomes primary target. Doesn't understand the tension in the house. Loves exploring, collecting things, asking questions. Represents the innocent future both Satu and Andersen are fighting to protect. His existence is proof of Andersen's crime but also his path to redemption. Can become tragic victim if Hunters fail to protect him."},"_id":"493e55bff317f16d"}
{"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"conditions":[],"oppositionLevel":3,"gifts":[],"isMainNPC":false,"notes":"Gift: Walking Dead (act after final wound), Hook's crew from shipwreck","background":"","descriptors":["Lost souls seeking revenge, swollen rotten flesh"],"npcType":"villager","agenda":["Revenge on living"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1},"max":1}}},"name":"Dead Pirates","flags":{"scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","inspiration":"The Little Mermaid"},"type":"npc","_id":"5f999742684e5bb7"}
{"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"conditions":[],"oppositionLevel":3,"gifts":[],"isMainNPC":false,"notes":"Son of Andersen and Satu, unknowingly key to conflict","background":"","descriptors":["Lively child who can never sit still"],"npcType":"villager","agenda":["Understand who Andersen is"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1},"max":1}}},"name":"Erik","flags":{"scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","inspiration":"The Little Mermaid"},"type":"npc","_id":"60ecdf09e363746a"}
{"name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-cat.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Adam is a young man in his twenties who works on Andersen's estate to pay off a debt he owes to the former commander. Unlike the twenty-plus other servants who can come and go freely, Adam cannot escape to the nearby city—he is bound by his obligation until the debt is cleared. Despite his circumstances, Adam is remarkably talkative and sociable, perhaps because he craves connection and conversation to break up the monotony of estate work. He observes everything that happens in the household and has no qualms about sharing gossip with visitors, including the Hunters. Adam knows there is a complex and troubled relationship between Andersen and Satu, and he's observed that the woman comes from the Captain's past, though he doesn't know the sordid details. He's also noticed that Andersen is very considerate of young Erik and clearly regards the boy as a son, though again Adam doesn't know why. Adam provides the Hunters with useful social intelligence about the estate's inhabitants and dynamics. He can be encountered wandering the estate grounds and will eagerly approach visitors to chat.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a talkative young servant bound by debt to Andersen","I observe everything that happens on this estate","I enjoy conversation and sharing what I know","I cannot leave the estate until my debt is paid"],"gifts":[],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Pass the time by talking with interesting visitors","Eventually pay off my debt and return to the city","Understand the strange dynamics between Andersen, Satu, and Erik"],"notes":"Adam serves as an information source for Hunters exploring the estate. Voice: Fast-talking, gossipy, friendly. Encountered on a roll of 5-6 when exploring estate. Provides social context: complex relationship between Andersen and Satu, they have a shared past, Andersen treats Erik like a son. Doesn't know about the rape, murder, or Enar's return—just observes surface behavior. Over 20 servants work on the estate but most are inexperienced fighters and would flee if Enar attacks. Only Andersen and Christian are skilled combatants. Adam himself is not a fighter. Willing to help Hunters in non-combat ways (showing them around, delivering messages, providing supplies). Represents the ordinary people caught up in extraordinary circumstances."},"_id":"97a5a74838cd094c"}
{"name":"Andersen - The Former Commander","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills","In addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter"],"agenda":["Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents","Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man","Prevent anyone from discovering what I have done"],"gifts":[{"name":"Commander","description":"Andersen is skilled at giving orders and managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen can issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional Success (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it."}],"background":"Andersen is a former military commander who now lives on a luxurious estate near Sundsvall. Six years ago, he led a company of soldiers that included Enar. When Andersen discovered that Enar and the dancer Satu were in love, he became consumed with jealousy. Andersen abused his authority, raping Satu and then falsely accusing Enar of abandoning his post. As punishment, Enar was chained to rocks and left to drown in the sea. The injustice drove Enar to become an immortal monster seeking revenge. Unknown to Enar, Andersen fathered a son with Satu—Erik—whom Andersen now raises as his own. Andersen has tried to atone for his crimes by becoming a benefactor, but his past has caught up with him as Enar systematically hunts down and kills all members of the former company.","notes":"Andersen is a skilled commander capable of coordinating defenses and enhancing allies with his orders. He genuinely wants to protect Satu and Erik, but his dark secret haunts him. He has a diary containing evidence of his crimes. If Erik is put in danger, Andersen will confess everything to save the child. The estate has ~20 servants but few can fight—defense relies on Andersen and Christian.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","inspiration":"The Little Mermaid - The Prince","role":"Former commander hiding dark secret, father to Erik, target of Enar's revenge"},"_id":"9c39042e78ac6515"}
{"name":"Satu - The Broken Dancer","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-armored-leather-grey.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Satu was once a beautiful and talented dancer in Vaasa, a small Finnish coastal town, where she performed and brought joy to audiences. Six years ago, she fell deeply in love with Private Enar, a young Carolean soldier stationed there. When Enar deserted to stay with her, his comrades discovered him and Captain Andersen ordered his brutal execution—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea. Satu never knew the true extent of Andersen's cruelty, only that Enar vanished. Then Andersen, mad with jealousy and obsession, returned and raped her. The assault left her pregnant with Erik. Andersen disappeared afterward, leaving Satu to sink into poverty, forced to work as an assistant cook while raising her son alone. Six years passed in hardship until Andersen—now retired and wealthy—sought her out, driven by guilt. Over months of effort, he earned her grudging forgiveness by freeing her from poverty and bringing her and Erik to live in his mansion. Satu now exists as a shadow of her former self, no longer dancing, barely speaking, accepting this life only because it provides safety and comfort for Erik. She suspects the monster appearing each night is Enar but hides from his gaze out of fear, shame, and confusion. She doesn't know if she wants him to succeed or fail. Her only certainty is that Erik—the sole reason she keeps going—must survive, even if it means staying with the man who destroyed her life.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a former dancer who has lost everything","I am but a shadow of my former self","I carry the trauma of what Andersen did to me","My son Erik is the only reason I keep going"],"gifts":[],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep going","Hide from Enar because I don't know how to face him after everything","Endure this life with Andersen for Erik's sake, even though it breaks me"],"notes":"Satu is a tragic figure—victim of both Andersen's violence and Enar's twisted love. Voice: Quiet, broken, rarely makes eye contact. She has guessed the monster is Enar but won't confront him out of fear and shame (she lives with his rapist/murderer). If Erik is endangered, both she and Andersen will sacrifice themselves to save him. If the truth comes out and Hunters offer her a choice, she may flee to the cliff to confront Enar alone (Day 3 potential). Her saying goodbye to Enar's heart at the sea bottom can give him peace (Sea Fairy can arrange this). She never dances anymore—that part of her died. Accepts life with Andersen not out of forgiveness but pragmatism for Erik's future. Complex feelings: grief for Enar, hatred for Andersen, love for Erik, shame for her circumstances. If Enar succeeds in 'merging' with her, it would be body horror—she would be trapped in a fusion of flesh and sea matter, conscious but unable to escape."},"_id":"c661efcb211f15f2"}
{"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"conditions":[],"oppositionLevel":5,"gifts":[],"isMainNPC":true,"notes":"Gift: Immune to behavior effects when carrying out orders, +1 OL when eliminating obstacles","background":"","descriptors":["Former soldier, cold determination"],"npcType":"villager","agenda":["Help Andersen, eliminate Enar"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1},"max":3}}},"name":"Christian the Relentless","flags":{"scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","inspiration":"The Little Mermaid"},"type":"npc","_id":"d2f25bfa9424cbbe"}
